<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Delegate Makes Speech at UNESCO Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 23 (Xinhua) -- China always attaches importance
to its relations with the United Nations Educational, Scientific
and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) and wishes to continue and
develop its long-term amicable cooperation with the organization
under condition of no obstacles, said a senior Chinese official
here today.
</P>
<P>
Wei Yu, vice president of the State Education Commission of
China and head of the Chinese delegation to the 29th session of
UNESCO General Conference being held in Paris, said that the major
responsibility of UNESCO is to advance the undertakings of
education, science, culture and communication among its member
states.
</P>
<P>
She said that UNESCO must respect the sovereignty of its member
states and the principle of cultural diversity in all its
activities, and should concentrate its efforts to promoting
international intellectual cooperation in its fields of competence
rather than acting beyond its fields of competence.
</P>
<P>
She said that considering the situation of education
development in many developing countries, UNESCO has to step up
its efforts in the field of education.
</P>
<P>
"UNESCO, an organization in which education is one of its most
important fields, should make even greater efforts in this
regard," she said.
</P>
<P>
She suggested that UNESCO lay more emphasis on assisting
developing countries in implementing urgently needed education
projects, such as making rural education better serve economic and
social development and thus giving fresh impetus to education
development in developing countries.
</P>
<P>
She said that the Chinese government will persist in its policy
under which economic growth should be based on giving priority to
educational development and thus improving the quality of people
and have as its driving force the advancement of science and
technology, and make more efforts to achieve integral progress of
all social services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
