<HEADLINE> Economic Empowerment of Women is Pakistan's Top </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Economic empowerment of
women, especially of rural women, is the top priority of the
Pakistani government, Minister of State for Women Development,
Social Welfare and Special Education Tahmina Daultana said today.
</P>
<P>
For this purpose, the government is taking a number of measures
to elevate the life standard of women, Tahmina said.
</P>
<P>
The rural women is over burden with work and almost all women
development efforts are mainly concentrated in cities, she said.
</P>
<P>
"We must bring the rural women's potential in the main-stream
in order to empower them for a safe and respectable life," she
said.
</P>
<P>
The government is establishing crisis centers for women in
distress and has enhanced its efforts for women education, she
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
