<HEADLINE> UAE Supports UN Agreement on Mine Clearance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates
today expressed its support for an agreement sponsored by the
United Nations on clearing mines in the world, the UAE's WAM news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Adil Mahfuz Khalifa, the representative of the UAE in the U.N.
Development Program, told the official news agency that his country
hailed the agreement as throttling "the terrible monster" which
has killed and maimed thousands of people, including children.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is expected to be signed by U.N. members during a
U.N. conference due to be held in Canada in December.
</P>
<P>
Khalifa said the UAE would make its best endeavors, including
financial help, to contribute to the implementation of the
agreement.
</P>
<P>
The clearance of mines which have killed and are still
threatening the lives of thousands of people in the world has
become a pressing task for the mankind. 
</P>
</TEXT>
