<HEADLINE> France Wishes Algerian Election Conducted in Good </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 23 (Xinhua) -- France today expressed its wish
that the local elections which began today in Algeria could go
ahead in "satisfying conditions."
</P>
<P>
"The local elections in Algeria make up a new step in the
institutional process engaged by the Algerian authorities in
1995," said French Foreign Ministry spokesman Jacques Rummelhardt.
</P>
<P>
Some 16 million Algerian voters went to polling stations today
for the fourth time in two years to elect some 15,000 local
representatives from 37 political parties.
</P>
<P>
"As we have already said several times before, we are favorable
to a political and democratic solution chosen by the Algerians
themselves to the crisis which the country knows," said the
Foreign Ministry spokesman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
