<HEADLINE> UK Chocolate Not Milky, Says MEPs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Members of the European
parliament (MEPs) today voted to force Britain to change the name
of its product "Milk Chocolate," according to a BBC report.
</P>
<P>
Apart from beef, milk chocolate is the latest British product
to suffer at the hands of Euro-MPs.
</P>
<P>
Reacting to the vote, Tory Euro-MPs condemned this as "a major
setback for British consumers."
</P>
<P>
With large majorities of Euro-MPs supporting key amendments
hurting British producers, the use of the term "Milk Chocolate" in
Britain is now under threat.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the vote, Tory consumer policy spokesman Caroline
Jackson warned, "Not only did considerable majorities of Euro-MPs
vote to change the name of British chocolate, they also supported
calls to set up a chocolate tasting center to decide what
chocolate is."
</P>
<P>
The Chocolate War has continued since 1973, when Britain joined
the EEC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
