<HEADLINE> Austria Grants Uganda Fund for Local Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The Austrian government has
donated to Uganda about 800,000 U.S. Dollars toward local
government elections to be held next month countrywide, reported
Radio Uganda today.
</P>
<P>
An agreement to this effect was signed here yesterday by
councillor and Head of the Austrian Embassy, regional bureau for
development cooperation in Uganda Mr. Antomea and UNDP resident
representative Babatundi Thomas.
</P>
<P>
Uganda is Africa's favor child in the western world and the
Austrian government is the first donor to grant Uganda funds
under the course-sharing arrangement coordinated by the United
Nations Development Program (UNDP).
</P>
<P>
UNDP has in the past coordinated donor funds for Uganda's
constituent assembly elections in the country in 1994 and
presidential and parliamentary elections in 1996.
The Austrian government supported the above elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
