<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Convention on Setting up WIPO Endorsed in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian parliament,
the House of People's Representatives today approved the
Convention on the establishment of the World Intellectual
Property Organization (WIPO).
</P>
<P>
An report from the Ethiopian News Agency said, Ethiopia, on
joining WIPO, could derive a number of benefits including access
to technical assistance in the form of publications, documents,
and information concerning industrial property specially those
relating to transfer of technology in addition to the
establishment of patent documentation services.
</P>
<P>
Membership to WIPO would also help foster local studies and
encourage foreign investors to take part in development
activities in the country, the report added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the house today also ratified three bills including
a loan agreement with the International Fund for Agricultural
Development and the accord between Ethiopia and Kuwait for the
avoidance of double taxation and the prevention of fiscal evasion.
</P>
</TEXT>
