A newsletter close to Algeria's bannned Islamic Salvation
Front on Wednesday denounced a 16.6 million U.S. dollars weapons
deal between Algeria and South Africa.
</P>
<P>
The newsletter called on South African President Nelson
Mandela to intervene, saying the arms would be used against the
Algerian people.
</P>
<P>
South Africa's National Conventional Arms Control Committee
and Denel today denied existence of such deal.
</P>
<P>
However, a statement from Denel last week said Algeria had
shown interest in buying the seeker surveillance system. 
</P>
