<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique's Province Prepared for Fighting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Niassa Province in northern
Mozambique has held a meeting recently to discuss how to
formulate policy and take measures against possible drought
caused by El Nino in the 1997/98 agricultural year, local press
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting attended by agriculture and fishery technical
personnel, non-governmental organizations and humanitarian bodies
decided to launch a publicity campaign to make people familiar
with El Nino and its possible effects and mobilize farmers to
expand area under cultivation and plant anti-drought crops.
</P>
<P>
According to the Mozambique Information Agency, some counties
of Niassa Province, such as Metarica, Nipepe, Maua, Marrupa and
Mecanhelas, might be affected by drought because of their
geographical position. 
</P>
</TEXT>
