<DOCNO> XIE19971024.0037 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Army Hit by New Neo-Nazi Scandal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 23 (Xinhua) -- German Defense Minister Volker
Ruehe today issued a statement condemning the neo-Nazi conduct of
some German soldiers which was recorded on a video made by his own
troops.
</P>
<P>
The video reportedly includes scenes depicting anti-Semitic and
anti-American statements, racist slogans and Nazi salutes made by
eight soldiers of Germany's 571st Mountain Infantry battalion.
</P>
<P>
There are also scenes showing burning ovens which are
apparently meant to depict the burning of Jews.
</P>
<P>
The video, reportedly made by members of the battalion three
years ago, was given to the Defense Ministry by the German SAT 1
television network which plans to broadcast it later today.
</P>
<P>
Describing the recorded scenes as "horrible performances,"
Ruehe said he would take swift disciplinary measures and seek
criminal proceedings against the soldiers involved.
</P>
<P>
Members of the same battalion based in the eastern German state
of Saxony gave rise to another scandal in July this year when a
video was aired on television showing seven soldiers carrying out
simulated executions and rapes. 
</P>
