<HEADLINE> Preparation of Food Security Program Finalized in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The nationwide preparation
of the food security program which is believed to guarantee food
security and bring about sustainable economic development has
been finalized, the Ministry of Agriculture of Ethiopia said
today.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, Belay Ejigu, head of
Extension Program Department in the ministry underlined the need
to produce sufficient food grains and strengthen the purchasing
power of the public and its maintenance if food security is to be
achieved.
</P>
<P>
He said at a meeting here that there is no belief that the
extension program now is full-swing with particular emphasis on
small holders alone could guarantee food security be it at the
family or national level.
</P>
<P>
The production in the previous year has seen surplus over the
national need, but it is impossible to say food security for all
has been achieved, he added.
</P>
<P>
Practical measures are now being taken to regularize the
extension program on the plots of all farmers, he said, adding
that the number of farmers incorporated in the package has now
reached over 650,000 against 33,000 two years ago.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, an official from the Disaster Prevention and
Preparedness Commission said at the meeting that his commission
has begun preparations to compile a document on drought prone
areas and the major reasons behind the phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, failure of rains this year has
exposed about 3.4 million people to food shortage and the country
has so far distributed over half of the 307,000 metric tons of
the food reserve it had. 
</P>
</TEXT>
