<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rosskopf Beats Kong in World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Germany's world No. 8 Jorg
Rosskopf upset No. 2 Kong Linghui of China, virtually qualifying
for the quarter-finals of the World Cup table tennis tournament in
Nimes on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Left-handed Rosskopf sent a crushing 21-6, 21-18 defeat to
Kong, Olympic doubles gold medalist and 1995 world champion.
</P>
<P>
Reigning world champion Jan-Ove Waldner of Sweden clinched his
second straight win by beating Frenchman Christophe Legout 21-13,
21-19.
</P>
<P>
Rosskopf, who won the European Masters Cup for the third time
last month, jumped to a 10-2 lead with strong shots from both
wings and wrapped up the first 21-6.
</P>
<P>
Kong fought to 10-7 in the second set, but Rosskopf won six
consecutive points to pull away to the victory.
</P>
<P>
Canada's world No. 13 Johnny Huang got an easy victory over
Oceania champion Peter Jackson of New Zealand 21-13, 21-9.
</P>
</TEXT>
