<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial on Arts Festival (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The Saturday edition of
People's Daily, China's leading newspaper, will carry an editorial
offering congratulations on today's opening of the Fifth China
Arts Festival.
</P>
<P>
The grand China Arts Festival is an influential national
cultural event which has been held four times since 1987,
according to the editorial entitled "Compose a New Chapter and
Greet the New Century".
</P>
<P>
The China Arts Festival has played a positive role in promoting
the prosperity and development of cultural and artistic
undertakings in China, and in promoting material, cultural and
ideological progress, according to the editorial.
</P>
<P>
The festival is particularly significant for being the last of
its kind this century, and for following the return of Hong Kong
to the motherland and the convocation of the 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
The festival will carry a theme based on patriotism, unity,
prosperity, and the collection of high quality cultural and
artistic works, and will display national culture, revitalization
of the national spirit, celebrations of the 15th CPC national
congress, and greeting the new century", according to the
editorial.
</P>
<P>
The festival program will demonstrate the mental features of
the Chinese people in greeting the new century with full
confidence and vigor.
</P>
<P>
The culture and art of the Chinese nation have a long history
which has witnessed continuous development. China has proceeded
under the guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory to score unprecedented
achievements in culture and art since start of the economic reform
drive in the late 1970s.
</P>
<P>
Superb cultural and artistic works have been produced in recent
years under the leadership of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China with Jiang Zemin at the core, the
editorial says.
</P>
<P>
Programs during the festival will feature China's achievements
in culture and art, according to the editorial.
</P>
</TEXT>
