<HEADLINE> France Provides 4,000 Metric Tons of Wheat to Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The government of France has
agreed to provide 4,000 metric tons of soft wheat to Nepal,
Nepal's official RSS news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, 25 percent of the proceeds from the sale
of the wheat within Nepal will be used to cover the cost of
internal transportation, while the rest will be used to finance
priority rural and agriculture development projects, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
France is a member of Nepal Aid Group.  
</P>
