<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Tourism Continues to Grow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 24 (Xinhua) -- China earned 7.47 billion US
dollars from tourism during the January-August period, up 13.58
percent on last year's same period, according to Cheng Wendong,
deputy director of the China National Tourism Administration.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony of a national tourism fair,
Cheng said that China hosted more than 4.77 million foreign
tourists for the period, up 10.54 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
He said it is possible for China to surpass the earnings target
of 11 billion US dollars by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Rising incomes and more leisure time have enabled Chinese
citizens to travel more frequently, said Cheng.
</P>
<P>
Projections call for China to earn over 180 billion yuan from
domestic tourism during 1997, said Cheng. He added that domestic
tourism accounts for some 66 percent of the total earnings for the
nation's tourism industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
