<HEADLINE> Dalian Hosts National Tourism Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 24 (Xinhua) -- A national tourism trade fair
opened today in Dalian, a coastal city in northeast China's
Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
Some 35-odd representative groups from 31 provinces, autonomous
regions and municipalities are attending the three-day fair
sponsored by National Tourism Administration, and the local
government.
</P>
<P>
Similar fairs in the past have greatly promoted domestic
tourism.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan Province in southwest China, and the southern provinces
of Guangdong and Hainan have witnessed respective annual tourism
growth rates of 21 percent, 26.2 percent and 48.7 percent, in
terms of the number of tourists.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan Province leads the nation with an annual earnings growth
rate for tourism of nearly 63 percent. 
