<P>
Eastern plans to list a total of 300 million A shares to raise
more than 720 million yuan in domestic funds needed to purchase
passenger aircraft and support the construction of the
international airport in Shanghai's Pudong New Area.
</P>
<P>
Some 270 million shares will be offered to the public, with 30
million shares available for company employees.
</P>
<P>
China Eastern is listed in Hong Kong, and its American
Depository Receipts (ADR) are on the New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The company operates 40-odd passenger aircraft, each with 100
seats or more, including A300, MD-80 and MD-11 aircraft. Eastern,
which has ordered five A340 and nine MD-90 passenger aircraft,
offers more than 120 regularly scheduled flights to more than 50
domestic and foreign cities.
</P>
<P>
The company expects both its 1997 business turnover and net
income to rise by 20 percent on 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
