<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fifth China Arts Festival Opens Tomorrow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The Fifth China Arts Festival
will open in this capital of southwest China's Sichuan Province,
tomorrow evening as scheduled.
</P>
<P>
The organizing committee has prepared to host approximately
10,000 people expected to either attend or perform during the
Festival, and the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR)
will send its first-ever delegation to the festival.
</P>
<P>
Visitors attending the festival, which will run from October 25
to November 5, will have the rare opportunity to enjoy 32
performnces by artists from both at home and overseas, including
artists from Taiwan, Macao and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Mass gatherings, and song and dance performnces, which will be
held in the Tianfu Square in the downtown area, will feature
artists from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Chengdu has built this new downtown square at a cost of 300
million yuan (36 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The goal of the China Arts Festival, a biennial event which is
the largest showcase of the country's artistic achievements and
art styles from different localities. is to promote folk culture
and improve national spirit.
</P>
<P>
This year's fifth fair will be the last of this century.
</P>
<P>
Internet surfers can gain up-to-the-minute information about
the festival as part of China's first-ever effort to use the net
to promote a national arts festival.
</P>
<P>
Organizers will provide information related to famous artists
and ensembles, as well as sound bites and photographs. The
material will be available in both English and Chinese at
HTTP://WWW.SC.CNINFO.NET/5THART/INDEX, a web site linked to the
New York Times.
</P>
<P>
The organizing committee set up a new media center at a cost of
more than two million yuan (241,000 US dollars). The facility will
provide journalists with easy access to telephones, fax machines
and TV sets.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the media center will provide the press with easy
access to the web site. 
</P>
</TEXT>
