<HEADLINE> Strobl, Piccard Win Opening Races of World Cup Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Josef Strobl of Austria and Leila
Piccard of France won the opening races of the new World Cup
skiing season at Tignes on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Strobl won the men's parallel race after beating such famous
skiiers like Alberto Tomba, Luc Alphand and Kjetil-Andre Aamodt of
Norway.
</P>
<P>
In the head-to-head final against Aamodt, Strobl proved himself
much better than Aamodt by winning the race in a margin of 1.49
seconds.
</P>
<P>
Piccard's victory was a surprise as she had not won a single
World Cup race before Friday's competitions.
</P>
<P>
Piccard, sister of former downhill Olympic champion Franck
Piccard, had only a couple of podium places to her record and won
the bronze medal for the giant slalom at the world championships
in Sestrieres.
</P>
<P>
But the 26-year-old from Les Saisies still managed to beat
unheralded Swede Ylva Nowen in the final. Nowen had an easy path
to the final, taking advantage from two disqualifications after
beating double world champion Deborah Compagnoni in the first
round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
