with a speech entitle "Norway and China: Partners in a Changing
World". He said that the constantly increasing trade volume
between the two countries since the 1990s, and pointed to expanded
areas of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He cited Norway as a strong supporter of China's entry into
the World Trade Organization (WTO), and said that China's
membership in the organization will not only help promote the
country's continued economic development, but will also benefit
the multilateral trade system.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said, the Norwegian government will continue its
efforts to stimulate trade and economic relations with China.
</P>
<P>
Norwegian King Harald V attended a luncheon at noon today and
introduced a campaign to promote Norway's fisheries sector.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises in the two countries signed three cooperative
agreements.  
