<HEADLINE> Exhibition of Agricultural Achievements Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- A national exhibition of the
achievements in comprehensive agricultural development over the
past ten years was opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Chunyun, a member of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China and Vice Premier of the
State Council, Wang Bingqian, vice-chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress, cut the ribbon for
the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural comprehensive development involves the development
of hills, water, farmland, forests and roads within a project
area, and is intended to improve the quality of the low-yield
farmland and raise the production of grain, cotton, edible oil,
meat and sugar.
</P>
<P>
The development program, launched in 1988, covers 1,310
counties and 270 state-run farms across China.  
