<HEADLINE> Hoyer-Larsen Top Seed at Hong Kong Open Badminton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Denmark's Veteran Poul-Erik
Hoyer-Larsen has been ranked as the top seed for the men's singles
at the 1997 Millennium Hong Kong Open Badminton Championships set
to open here next Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Second and third on the seeding list for the men's singles are
Hoyer-Larsen's compatriots Peter Gade Christensen and Peter
Rasmussen. Hoyer-Larsen is now ranked third and Christensen and
Rasmussen are fifth and sixth in the world.
</P>
<P>
Seeded first to third for the women's singles at the five-day,
170,000 U.S. dollars event are Judith Meulendijks from the
Netherlands, Lee Kyung Won from South Korea and Cindana of
Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Entered in the International Badminton Federation-sanctioned,
five-star event are 123 players from 15 countries and regions
including China, Indonesia, Thailand, Denmark, South Korea, Japan
and Hong Kong which is China's Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
On the competition program are men's and women's singles,
doubles and mixed doubles events.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Open, 13th on its annual series, is one of the 22
events worldwide on the IBF-sanctioned World Grand Prix
series. Players who earn enough points in the series are to be
invited to the World Grand Prix Finals set for the end of this
year in Jakarta, Indonesia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
