<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The Tokyo Motor Show opened today
to showcase 771 vehicles and motorcycles sent in by 38 Japanese,
South Korean, U.S. and European manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
The biannual event, currently the 32nd, is taking place at the
Makuhari Messe convention center near the city of Chiba, southeast
of Tokyo, and was scheduled to last 13 days.
</P>
<P>
While representatives of 330 automakers from 14 countries were
at the opening ceremony, visitors, mostly Japanese, are expected
to total 1.5 million throughout the show.
</P>
<P>
The Japan Motor Industrial Federation (JMIF), the organizer,
took the chance to highlight the industry's trend -- innovation
for environmentally friendly cars.
</P>
<P>
"The Earth demands that we treasure ... the environment, and
cleverly use its limited resources with loving care," the JMIF
said in a statement to the press.
</P>
<P>
The show was opened five weeks before Japan is to host an
international conference on global warming, which stems partly
from carbon dioxide emissions.
</P>
<P>
What many automakers want visitors to notice are their latest
models' high "fuel efficiency" and "compactness," which enable
smaller and cleaner emissions. 
