<HEADLINE> Japan Becomes Major Investor in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Japan is currently the
largest investor in China, with contracted investments of 27.6
billion US dollars by the end of June, according to Yozo Okumoto,
a Japanese banker.
</P>
<P>
Japan invested 15.85 billion US dollars in 15,670 projects in
China during the period.
</P>
<P>
Okumoto said that overseas investors have invested 15.85
billion US dollars in 294,000 projects in China between the late
1970s when the country opened itself to the outside world and the
end of June this year.
</P>
<P>
Okumoto made the remarks at a seminar marking the 25th
anniversary of the normalization of Sino-Japanese relations.
</P>
<P>
The delegation's visit is the 22nd since the first visit by a
Japanese banking delegation in 1977.  
</P>
