<HEADLINE> China's Three-Quarter Tax Revenue up 18.5 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- China's industrial and
commercial tax revenue grew 18.5 percent year-on-year to more than
536.5 billion yuan for the January-September period, according to
the State Administration of Taxation (SAT) today.
</P>
<P>
The total amount represented 77.2 percent of this year's
official target, the SAT said.
</P>
<P>
A breakdown shows that the central government tax revenue
reached 302 billion yuan in the first nine months, up 20.9 percent
from a year ago, while the local tax revenue rose 15.5 percent to
more than 234.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the sustained and steady growth of the
national economy has provided a guarantee for the relatively rapid
increase in the tax revenue.
</P>
<P>
Between January and September, China's gross domestic product
grew nine percent from the same period of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
