<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Korea Provides Loan to Philippine Airport Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Korea will provide a 25 million
U.S. dollar loan to an airport project in the southern
Philippines, the Philippine News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The loan, which will finance the proposed Laguindingan
International Airport in Mindanao, has a payable time of 30 years,
including a grace period of 10 years, at a 2.5 percent interest
rate.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Foreign Affairs Secretary Domingo Siazon and Korean
Ambassador to Manila Chang Choon-Lee Thursday exchanged note on
the implementation of the airport project, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be disbursed over 48 months from the date of
signing of the loan agreement to ensure speedy implementation of
the project. The agreement signing date will be arranged soon by
the Department of Finance and the Korean embassy in Manila.
</P>
<P>
The Laquindingan International Airport will be constructed on a
300-hectare area within the Zone of Peace and Development in
Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
It is envisioned to serve the transportation needs of around
three million people in five provinces and expand the
transportation and communications network in the region.
</P>
<P>
The airport is designed to provide obstruction-free aviation
operations, reduce incidence of water-related flight cancellations
and allow the handling of A-300 and similar wide-bodied aircraft
in the region.
</P>
<P>
The project is also expected to stimulate business and
investment growth and contribute further to the economic
development and promotion of peace and stability in Southern
Philippines.  
</P>
</TEXT>
