<HEADLINE> Swiss Bank Clears Philippine President on Deposit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 24 (Xinhua) -- A Swiss bank has issued a
certification that Philippine President Fidel Ramos has no bank
account or any relationship deposits with the bank, a news release
from the Philippine Presidential Palace said today.
</P>
<P>
In the same certification, the Swiss Bank Julius Baer &AMP; Co.
Ltd. also said that the Philippine National Oil Company (PNOC) has
no bank account or relationship with it.
</P>
<P>
The certification was conveyed by the bank to the American
lawyer of the Philippine Government, Stephen Bomse.
</P>
<P>
Ramos earlier authorized the bank to disclose, if any bank
account or any bank relationship, under a waiver that he and PNOC
signed in order that the bank secrecy may not be invoked.
</P>
<P>
Lawyers of the victims of human right abuses in former
President Ferdinand Marcos' time earlier insinuated that Ramos
maintains an account in the Swiss bank.
</P>
<P>
They claimed that Ramos has transferred some of the fabled
1,241 tons of Marcos' gold deposited in Swiss banks to a bank
account owned by himself in the Swiss bank.
</P>
<P>
Ramos has dismissed the claims for several times, saying that
he has no bank deposit in Switzerland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
