<HEADLINE> Haze in Singapore Stays in Unhealthy Range </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The haze has returned to
Singapore and stayed in the unhealthy range for a third straight
day today, prompting the government to advise the elderly and the
weak to stay at home and refrain from vigorous outdoor activities.
</P>
<P>
The Pollutant Standard Index (PSI) reached 175 on Thursday, the
highest level this week. For today it peaked at 168 at 1 p.m.. The
Index has been over the 100-ponit level since Tuesday evening.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Environment said the situation is expected to
continue for at least another day or so and, therefore advised the
elderly and persons with heart or respiratory diseases to reduce
physical and outdoor activities. The general population should
reduce vigorous outdoor activities, it said.
</P>
<P>
However, the Ministry also said that some improvement is likely
over the weekend as a change in wind direction and more showers
are expected in the region.  
</P>
</TEXT>
