<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Chief Executive Returns From Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, chief
executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) of
China, returned here today after paying a visit to Brussels and
London.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival at the airport, Tung told reporters that his
visit was fruitful.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Tung met with political leaders of Belgium
and Britain, leaders of the European Union (EU), members of the
European Parliament and people of the industrial and commercial
community in Europe.
</P>
<P>
Tung said he had briefed these people on Hong Kong's situation
after its return to China and all the people he had met extended
their congratulations on Hong Kong's smooth return to the
motherland and expressed their confidence in the future of Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said he had briefed leaders of the EU and Britain on Hong
Kong's development prospects.
</P>
<P>
"The EU and Britain are very important for Hong Kong's economic
development and we would like to strengthen the cooperation
between Hong Kong and Europe," Tung added.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in London, Tung held meetings with British
Prime Minister Tony Blair and Foreign Secretary Robin Cook, who
said Britain attaches great importance to the relations between
Britain and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong can serve as a bridge for the Sino-British relations,
which will benefit Britain, China and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the fluctuation of the stock market, Tung said the
SAR government is determined to maintain the Hong Kong dollar's
peg to the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
He said Hong Kong's economic foundation is good and the
speculation might affect Hong Kong's stock market in the short
term, but can not succeed in the long run.  
</P>
</TEXT>
