<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Investors Urged to Stay Calm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 24 (Xinhua) -- A well-known local economist said
that the financial market fluctuations in Hong Kong will not have
much effect on the stability of Macao's financial system and that
investors should stay calm.
</P>
<P>
Lao Pun-Lap, secretary-general of the Macao Society of
Economics Study, told the "Macao Daily News" that investors need
not worry too much about the market fluctuations in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said that interest rates rise in Hong Kong would only have
a short-term negative effect on the economic growth, especially, the
real estate sector. But he said the rates will drop when the Hong
Kong dollar is stabilized.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong has a sound financial management system," he said.
"It also has plenty of treasury and foreign currency reserves. The
government intervention will help stabilize the Hong Kong dollar
very soon, and (the fluctuations) will have little impact on
Macao."
</P>
<P>
Lao said that investors need not panic at what happened in the
stock market as Hong Kong economic growth will be maintained and
most listed companies are reporting profits.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that investors stay calm and not sell out their
stocks in panic, otherwise they will suffer greater losses. They
should keep at hands shares of those companies that have great
development potential. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
