<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Rebound Slightly on Philippine Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine stock market
today reversed a sharp decline at early trading and rebounded
slightly thanks to "good news" from the Hong Kong market, traders
said.
</P>
<P>
The 30-share Philippine Stock Exchange Index (Phisix), the
benchmark index for the bourse, plunged nearly 70 points within
one hour after trading opened today.
</P>
<P>
But it arrested the sharp downturn and moved upward due to a
big rebound in the Hong Kong market, which opened later than the
local exchange. The Phisix closed at 1,847.78 points, up 14.87
from Thursday's close.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, the Phisix nose-dived to a four-year low of
1,832.91 after losing 96.06 points or nearly 5 percent due to a
crash at the Hong Kong market. Due to widespread worries over an
expanded and prolonged regional currency turmoil, the Phisix had
been falling since Monday.
</P>
<P>
Traders attributed today's upswing to a technical rebound,
which they doubted can be sustained next week.
</P>
<P>
They said after investors will shift their attention from Hong
Kong to Thailand next week and what will happen in Thailand will
affect the region's sentiments.
</P>
<P>
Investors are now keeping a wary eye on Thailand where the
government has been urged to resign to take the blame for the
current protracted financial crisis, which has been hounding the
country since early this year.
</P>
<P>
All subindices ended today in the positive territory, with the
mining and property sectors posting the biggest gains of 43.98
points and 27.54 points, respectively, to end at 3,045.82 and
851.08.
</P>
<P>
Value turnover improved slightly on Thursday's close, reaching
1.12 billion pesos (32.4 million U.S. dollars), with a total of
1.7 billion shares changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Declines outnumbered advances, 59 to 53, while 39 others of the
151 traded issues remained standstill.  
</P>
</TEXT>
