<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Chief Executive: Speculators to Be Defeated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, chief
executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) of
China, said today that speculators against the Hong Kong dollar
would inevitably be defeated.
</P>
<P>
"We will make sure that they do not succeed in whatever they
are trying to do," he told reporters at the airport on his return
from a trip to Europe today, a day after the Hong Kong stock
market suffered its biggest ever one-day fall on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Tung said speculators had "decided to have a go" in Hong Kong
after successful attacks on other regional currencies, but his
government is committed to maintaining the Hong Kong dollar's peg
to the U.S. dollar, or the linked exchange rate.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is different from Southeast Asian nations because its
economic fundamentals are very good, it has the third largest
foreign exchange reserves in the world in addition to its huge
fiscal reserves and a large budget surplus and its economy
continues expanding, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Most of the listed companies in Hong Kong will enjoy a
double-digit growth, he added.
</P>
<P>
He praised SAR Financial Secretary Donald Tsang for his
management of this particular situation to defend the HK dollar.
</P>
<P>
The stability of the HK dollar lies in Hong Kong's economic
stability, Tung said. "As we move forward to make sure that the
linked exchange rate is to be maintained, we try to stop the
speculative attack on the HK dollar and we have really very good
professional management which responds very quickly to the attack.
The result of that is the increase in interest rates," he added.
</P>
<P>
Tung said the central government in Beijing had pledged support
for his government's efforts if necessary, but his government has
taken a series of measures which are effective in curbing
the speculation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
