<HEADLINE> Bulgaria's Investment Forum Attracts 2,000 Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, October 23 (Xinhua) -- More than 2,500 investors
gathered in Sofia, capital of Bulgaria, Thursday for the first
ever Bulgarian Investment Forum since the start of its economic
reform in 1989.
</P>
<P>
"Bulgaria has the necessary conditions for economic growth,"
President Stoyanov said while addressing the Forum.
</P>
<P>
He hoped investors would not only study figures and economic
indicators but also get to know the spirit of Bulgarian people and
their desire for change.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the nation had achieved consensus on
implementing the structural reform, which he viewed as an
irreversible process in the nation.
</P>
<P>
He said the transparent and speedy privatization that must be
completed by the end of 1998 was the key element of the structural
reform.
</P>
<P>
Other elements included reduction of public sector loses,
stabilization of the banking system and the improvement of
investment climate, which he pledged to work for.
</P>
<P>
The Forum was organized by the Foreign Investment Agency on the
initiative on the Bulgarian government and is likely to become the
top event on Bulgaria's 1997 economic calendar. 
