<HEADLINE> Final Preparations For China's Xiaolangdi Damming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAOLANGDI, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The largest water
conservation project on China's Yellow River today had its last
bit of blasting this morning before the river gets dammed.
</P>
<P>
Forty tons of explosives were used to move 125,000 cubic meters
of stone.
</P>
<P>
Fifty thousand cu.m. of stones that are a meter in diameter
have been accumulated for the damming.
</P>
<P>
Two cofferdams have been dismantled and the damming will start
on Sunday, and be completed on Tuesday. Some 90,000 cu.m. of stone
is expected to be dumped at the mouth of the dam, which is 106
m. wide.  
</P>
