<HEADLINE> Toshiba Mulls Tie-up With Chinese Firm on DVD Players </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Toshiba Corp, a leading Japanese
electronics maker, is considering a linkup with China's Sichuan
Changhong Electronics Group Corp. on digital videodisk players and
other consumer electronics products, Kyodo News reported.
</P>
<P>
The two companies are exploring possible cooperation over DVD
players, audiovisual equipment, washing machines, and
refrigerators, among other options, under a basic agreement on
comprehensive collaboration reached in August, Kyodo quoted a
Toshiba official as saying today.
</P>
<P>
Toshiba, which currently supplies color television components
to Changhong, China's largest home electronics company
based in Mianyang in Sichuan Province, could transfer DVD
technology and commission product and sales of DVD players in
China to the Chinese company, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Toshiba plans selling DVD players in China within a year or so,
though a specific date is not set, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
Toshiba started selling DVD players in Southeast Asia in summer
after releasing them in Japan in November last year. 
</P>
