<DOCNO> XIE19971024.0124 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Inflation Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 24 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's inflation
rate dropped to eight percent in September, the lowest level in a
year, according to the Central Statistical Service.
</P>
<P>
Local daily The Star today quoted economists as saying that
the drop from August's 8.7 percent was expected and the capital
market showed limited reaction to a figure that had largedly been
discounted before Thursday's announcement.
</P>
<P>
"Owing to high bases in the second half of last year, the
inflation rate should continue on its steep downward path for the
remainder of the year," economist Chantal Friedman said.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate in December last year registered 11.6
percent.
</P>
<P>
Friedman forecast inflation to drop below 7.5 percent in
October and November, with inflation "significantly below seven
percent at year-end".
</P>
<P>
She calculated the average inflation rate for this year at 8.7
percent and for next year at six percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
