<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines' Manufacturing Sector Recovers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' manufacturing
industry sustained its recovery in August, with its value and
volume indices both rising considerably from the year-ago levels,
the National Statistics Office said today.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the same period last year, the sector's value of
production index (VPI) went up 5.7 percent in August to 485.5 and
its volume of production index (VoPI) grew 3.9 percent to 162.11,
according to figures released by the office.
</P>
<P>
On a month-on-month comparison, the VPI registered an increase
of 2.9 percent from 471.7 in July.
</P>
<P>
Every month, the statistics office conducts a survey of 442 key
enterprises in the manufacturing sector to determine their
performance that will show the industry's contribution to the
country's gross national product (GNP).
</P>
<P>
Annual increases in the VPI were observed in nine out of the 16
major sectors covered by the survey, with electrical machinery
leading all sectors with a 54.9 percent growth.
</P>
<P>
Electrical machinery contributed 70.1 percent to the overall
annual growth of the manufacturing VPI during the period in
review. The sharp growth in this subsector was attributed to the
gains in the production of microcircuits.
</P>
<P>
On a monthly basis, the electrical machinery sector also
registered the highest increase of 12.1 percent, contributing 28.9
percent to the monthly VPI growth of the whole manufacturing
industry.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the VoPI increased by 2.6 percent from 157.9 in
July. The VoPI is a measure of change in volume net of inflation.
</P>
<P>
The manufacturing sector, representing nearly 23 percent of the
country's GNP, registered poor performance during the first
quarter. But it began to pick up in May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
