<HEADLINE> Master of Peking Opera To Be Remembered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Beijing will commemorate the
150th anniversary of the birth of a renowned master of Peking
Opera in early December.
</P>
<P>
Tan Xinpei, who was an outstanding figure in the history of
Peking Opera, contributed greatly to improving the art form and
was regarded as a "grand master" of the opera.
</P>
<P>
Many well-known Peking Opera actors and actresses, including
Tan's great-grandson, Tan Yuanshou, will give performances and
attend academic symposiums in memory of the operatic figure.
</P>
<P>
Commemorative activities will also be held in Tan's hometown of
Wuhan, the capital of Hubei province. 
