<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Hold International Week of Science and Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- China will hold its
International Week of Science and Peace on Nov. 9-16 to promote
scientific and technological development and world peace.
</P>
<P>
The theme of this week will focus on population, environment,
resources and sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
At today's news conference, Chen Yixiong, secretary-general of
the China Organizing Committee of the International Week of
Science and Peace, said that China has made this an annual event
since 1989.
</P>
<P>
This year's activities will include scientific and
technological fairs, academic lectures, exhibitions and film week,
held in more than a dozen large cities in China. Some scientific
laboratories and museums will be open to students, Chen said.
</P>
<P>
In 1988, the 43rd United Nations General Assembly passed a
resolution, deciding the week including Nov. 11 in every year be
declared International Week of Science and Peace. During that
time, the member countries should hold activities propagating the
important role science and technology plays in the maintenance of
world peace and social development.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 diplomatic envoys to China and representatives
from the U.N. will attend the opening ceremony which will be held
in the Great Hall of the People in Beijing on Nov. 11.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
