<HEADLINE> Book Fair Displays Publications on Tibet, Religion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Readers are amazed at piles of
religious books and books about Tibet at the "Golden Autumn" Book
Fair held at the Tao Fen Book Center of the SDX Joint Publishing
Company in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the China International Cultural Association, the
Chinese Publishers' Association and the SDX Joint Publishing
Company, the fair displays about 500 kinds of books about
religion and 600 titles about Tibet, among its total of 5,000
titles of academic and cultural books.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Chinese scholars have stepped up studies of
world religion. They have also translated some foreign works on
religion, including "Talking About the Bible", "Common Knowledge
About the Bible", "Christian Stories" and "Biblical Aphorisms".
</P>
<P>
"It's hard to see such books in bookstores in western
countries, for publishing such books often means lossing
money," said a Chinese scholar on the history of world
religion. "It reflects China's respect for religious beliefs
of its citizens."
</P>
<P>
The fair also highlights the publications on tibet and Tibet
studies, with a variety of books on Tibet's history, folk customs,
population, language, art, water conservancy, soil, vegetation,
medicine and science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Wang Jiu, director of the Tibetan People's Publishing House,
said that in the spirit of "inheriting and developing the
Tibetan culture," his publishing house has published one
collection of translated works on Tibetan studies a year since
1989. Meanwhile it also publishes foreign books on Tibetan studies
and now 12 such collections have been published.
</P>
<P>
Among the publications, "The Collection of Chinese Language
Literature on Tibetan Studies" by the Tibetan Academy of Social
Sciences has the first-hand material on Tibetan questions from the
early Qing Dynasty to the early years of the Republic of
China (1912-1949).
</P>
<P>
An old overseas Chinese man was overjoyed to find "A
comprehensive Bibliography of Tibet Studies" at the
fair. According to him, the book was the first of its kind in the
world and scholars on Tibetan studies in the world value it very
much.
</P>
<P>
"Over several decades, those who advocate the independence of
Tibet haven't published even one quality book on Tibet's culture
and religion except political pamphlets against China," he said.
</P>
<P>
The book fair will run through December 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
