<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Farmers Benefit from Scientific Farming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Jiangsu Province in east China
has made headway in breeding aquatic products in rice fields,
which has produced profits from both farming and breeding.
</P>
<P>
The province now has made use of 66,600 hectares of its rice
fields to breed fish, shrimps, crabs, soft-shelled turtles and
frogs.
</P>
<P>
Seventy percent of the fields have been used for breeding fish
and 826 hectares for breeding high-yield aquatic products.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu has two million hectares of rice fields, 400,000
hectares of which can be used for breeding. 
