<DOCNO> XIE19971024.0156 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pudong Vows to Build First-Class International Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Construction is in full swing
on a new first-class international airport to relieve air traffic
congestion in Shanghai, local sources said.
</P>
<P>
The gigantic project on the eastern edge of Shanghai, covering
an area of 32 square kilometers and designed to contain four
runways and four terminal buildings, will be able to handle 70
million passengers and 5 million tons of goods when completed.
</P>
<P>
The first-phase construction, scheduled to be completed in
1999, includes a 4,000-meter runway and a 280,000-square-meter
terminal building able to accommodate 20 million passengers and
750,000 tons of freight. The first-phase construction is expected
to cost 12 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The new airport will augment Hongqiao International Airport on
the western edge of Shanghai which handled 12.35 million
passengers last year, far exceeding its designed capacity of 9.6
million.
</P>
<P>
The new project is being built under designs provided by Paris
Airport Company of France, which was awarded the bid over 29 other
international competitors.
</P>
<P>
"The designs take into consideration Shanghai as an
international financial, trade and economic center in the 21st
century," one spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
