<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Heihe Develops Export-Oriented Farming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Export-oriented farming in
Heihe, a city in northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, is
experiencing vigorous growth because of its natural resources.
</P>
<P>
Heihe exported about 9.4 million kilograms of vegetable and
fruits to neighboring Russia between January and May of this year.
</P>
<P>
Great demand for vegetables and fruits by the east part of
Russia has provided opportunities for the city to develop
export-oriented agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The city has brought 37,500 square meters of agricultural land
on line to produce vegetable seedlings, 160,000 square meters for
hot-houses and 6,000 hectares for planting vegetable and
fruits. The annual output of these fields is 150 million kilograms.
</P>
<P>
The city has built the largest storehouse in northeast China
for fresh vegetables. Storage capacity exceeds 1.3 million
kilograms.
</P>
<P>
So far, more than 20 kinds of agricultural products such as
beans and livestock have been exported to Russia. The city's
annual export volume is estimated at 715 million yuan (89 million
U.S. dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
