<HEADLINE> Teleconference Makes Long-Distance Medical Care Possible </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 24 (Xinhua) -- China's first wireless
long-distance consultation system, similar to a teleconference,
now makes it possible for a patient to stay at home and still
receive a doctor's treatment.
</P>
<P>
This long-distance medical care system has been instituted by
Shanghai Medicine University (SMU).
</P>
<P>
SMU has used the system to provide long-distance medical
consultation services in the No. 1 People's Hospital in Jingjiang,
a city in Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The wireless system can transmit 15 to 18 pictures per
minute. Experts can see each other on the screen, and give advice
on a specific illness. X-rays, electrocardiograms and ultrasound
photos can be shown on the screen if necessary.
</P>
<P>
The wireless system offers many advantages for residents of
remote areas of China. Tianjin and other areas in southern China's
Hainan Province have asked SMU to extend the service. 
</P>
</TEXT>
