<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Ag-Science Companies Popular at Chinese Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, October 24 (Xinhua) -- A Ukrainian economic affairs
councilor in China, speaking at the China Jiangbei International
Agricultural Technological Fair in Qingdao, said that agricultural
machinery co-operation between the two countries has a good future.
</P>
<P>
The fair was held recently by the Ministry of Agriculture, the
State Science and Technology Commission, and the Qingdao Municipal
government as the only regularly-held agricultural fair at state
level. It attracted 14 agronomy institutes and companies from the
US, Japan, Germany and the Republic of Korea (ROK), and a group of
10 big Ukrainian agronomy institutes.
</P>
<P>
The official said that some Ukrainian businessmen think that,
since China still relies on manual labor for large-scale corn
harvesting, the market potential for the type of machinery on
display at the event is great. Also included were new foreign
agricultural products, high-quality seeds, fertilizer, irrigation
technology, and chemical products.
</P>
<P>
ROK's LG showed cultivation machinery that was well-received by
Chinese farmers. The Alaska 2000-type greenhouse and irrigation
equipment and technology of an Israeli and a US company also were
welcomed.
</P>
<P>
Farmers flocked to one of the exhibits that featured vegetable,
flower, and plant seeds from Germany's Agricultural Machinery and
Transportation Technological Trade Corp. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Chinese firms and foreign companies did a total of 90 million
US dollars worth of new technology and product deals. The
councilor says that, because of the fair's success he hopes to
establish a special institute to explore China's agro-technology
market.
</P>
<P>
Some agricultural officials from foreign embassies of developed
countries in China have contacted fair organizers to get
additional information. 
</P>
</TEXT>
