<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Meets Agricultural Minister of Netherlands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Sino-Netherlands agricultural
cooperation has broad development prospects, Chinese Vice-Premier
Jiang Chunyun told Minister of Agriculture of the Netherlands
J.J. Van Aartsen here today.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting in Zhongnanhai, headquarters of the
central government, Jiang said that as a big agricultural country
China has made great progress. However, he said prospects are even
brighter for development because the country's farming potential
has not been fully exploited.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands has a well-developed agricultural base, Jiang
said, boasting advanced farming technology and management
expertise.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that China will further open up its agricultural
sector to the outside world by stepping up exchanges and
cooperation with other countries.
</P>
<P>
Van Aartsen said the two countries have had successful
cooperation in the field of agriculture. The completion of two
jointly built training and demonstration centers in Beijing and
Shanghai showed the fruitfulness and smooth process of bilateral
cooperation in agriculture, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes that the two countries will strengthen
cooperation in research and the training of management personnel.
</P>
<P>
Van Aartsen and his entourage attended the inauguration
ceremony of the Animal Husbandry Training and Demonstration Center
in Beijing on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
They will attend the opening ceremony of a training and
demonstration center in Shanghai on Oct. 27.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Agriculture Minister Liu Jiang attended today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
Van Aartsen arrived in Beijing today as Liu Jiang's guest.
</P>
</TEXT>
