<HEADLINE> Stocks of China Telecom (HK) Float in HK, NY </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- China Telecom (Hong Kong)
Co. Ltd. became China's largest fundraiser through stocks after it
successfully raised 4 billion U.S. dollars on overseas stock
markets.
</P>
<P>
Telecom's stocks began trading this week on exchanges in Hong
Kong and New York.
</P>
<P>
In its initial public offering, Telecom made a public offering
of 2.6 billion shares at an issue price of 11.8 Hong Kong dollars,
raising 30.6 billion Hong Kong dollars (about 4 billion
U.S. dollars), 27.5 times its price-earnings ratio.
</P>
<P>
The public offering, which closed Oct. 16, was over-subscribed
by a factor of 30.
</P>
<P>
"The successful listing represents an important step for
China's highly state-monopolized telecommunications sector,"
market analysts here said.
</P>
<P>
Founded in March of this year, China Telecom underwent a
reorganization last month, absorbing the mobile phone assets in
Guangdong and Zhejiang provinces, thus pushing its total assets to
19 billion yuan (about 2.3 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Unlike other state telecommunication businesses, China Telecom
is an overseas-listed company incorporated strictly according to
international standards, though the state will hold 77.6 percent
of its total stakes with the rest owned by international
institutional investors and retail investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
