<HEADLINE> Taiyuan Curbs Cigar Advertisement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Taiyuan, capital of Shanxi
Province, has decided to gradually remove all cigarette billboards
in a bid to curb a "hazard to the health."
</P>
<P>
In another move, the city Bureau of Industry and Commerce, the
market watchdog, has resolved to tighten the approval process for
cigar advertisements.
</P>
<P>
Under the plan, all 69 cigar billboards in a major area of the
city will be demolished by the end of the month when contracts are
due. Billboards with longer contracts should be gone by end of the
year, a city spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
