<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shandong Achieves Dramatic Progress in Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Shandong Province's export volume
is expected to exceed 12 billion U.S. dollars by the end of this
year, said a spokesman for the gopvernment of the province in east
China.
</P>
<P>
Statistics showed that exports reached 9.94 billion U.S.
dollars in the first nine months of 1997, up 21.2 percent
over the figure for the same 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
So far, more than 10,400 overseas-funded enterprises are
operational in the province and 1,100 more have obtained the
export right, and 839 of them are production enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Exports of overseas-funded enterprises have topped 5.2 billion
U.S. dollars, up 36.4 percent over last year and 15 percent more
than the provincial average.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-funded enterprises have become an important factor in
the rapid development of the province's foreign trade.  
</P>
</TEXT>
