<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
tumbled today with the key market indicator suffering a slump of
5.35 percent, the biggest one-day fall in four years.
</P>
<P>
About 3 billion NZ dollars (1.86 billion U.S. dollars) in
shares value were wiped out as the market was responding to a
10-percent fall on the Hong Kong market on Thursday and sharp
falls on other markets.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index plunged 139 points to 2470 with a turnover of
89 million NZ dollars (55 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom shares led the falls, nose-diving 59 cents to 795
cents. Other leaders also dropped. Fletcher Energy declined 44
cents to 740 cents, Brierley Investment 7 cents to 128 cents,
Carter Holt Harvey  24 cents to 323 cents, Air New Zealand 17
cents to 258 cents and Lion Nathan 15 cents to 388 cents.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 150 falls and no rise.  
</P>
