<HEADLINE> US Homeownership Reaches A Record 66 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The homeownership rate in
the United States reached a record 66 percent during the third
quarter due in large part to the strong economy, Vice President Al
Gore said here today.
</P>
<P>
Gore said the new rate of homeownership, which was up from
65.7 percent in the second quarter of this year, broke the record
of 65.8 percent set during the third quarter of 1980.
</P>
<P>
It means that 66.7 million American families now own their own
homes, also the highest number in the U.S. history.
</P>
<P>
Gore told reporters in Washington that, while the economy was a
major contributor to the increases, the growth resulted in part
from the Clinton administration's fiscal policies, investment
priorities and overseas market openings.
</P>
<P>
