<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Air Force Averts Helicopter Disaster </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 24 (Xinhua) -- An attempt by Tamil rebels to
shoot down a Sri Lankan military helicopter carrying 35 soldiers
was aborted Thursday off the Mullaitivu coast in the northeast of
the country, security sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The rebels had targeted the helicopter from a sea craft but an
Mi-24 helicopter went quickly into action and destroyed the craft,
killing all the rebels on board.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the speedy action of the Mi-24 enabled the
transport helicopter to avert a major disaster.
</P>
<P>
At the time of the attack, the helicopter was moving troops
from Anuradhapura in North Central Province to a military camp in
Elephant Pass, Northern Province.
</P>
<P>
Though it was hit on one side of its tail, the chopper was able
to proceed to its destination.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting for a separate state of
their own in the north and east of the country for 14 years.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
