<HEADLINE> Quakes Jolt Bali, Mataram in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Two tectonic earthquakes
measuring 5.9 and 5.1 respectively on the Richter scale jolted
Indonesia's Bali Province and West Nusa Tenggara provincial
capital of Mataram Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quakes, which occurred at 9:16 a.m. local
time, was located in the Indian Ocean, about 60 kilometers
southeast of Selong, West Nusa Tenggara Province, according to the
Antara News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The severe tremor in Mataram lasted about 10 seconds, forcing
residents out of houses, shops and offices.
</P>
<P>
It was not immediately known how long the tremor lasted in
Bali.
</P>
<P>
An official of the provincial Meteorological and Geophysics
Agency, Sridah Budihardjo, said there was no immediate report on
casualties and material losses the earthquakes might have caused.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
