<HEADLINE> Summit of CIS Nations Finishes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The summit of the Commonwealth
of Independent States (CIS) concluded today in Chisinau, capital
of Moldova, without any resolutions being adopted.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference after the one-day meeting, Russian
President Boris Yeltsin said the CIS must be kept and
strengthened. He said the CIS would always exist.
</P>
<P>
Moldovan President Petr Luchinsky suggested that the CIS
nations carefully examine the free trade issue in order to work
out an accord which would be signed and implemented by all.
</P>
<P>
The meeting decided that the council of CIS heads of state will
hold regular meetings in March and October each year and a special
meeting of the council is scheduled for January 23,1998.
</P>
<P>
Since it was established nearly six years ago, the CIS has held
13 summit meetings with more than 500 resolutions adopted. Only a
few of these have been carried out. 
</P>
