<HEADLINE> Panama to Make Colon Free Zone One of Biggest in Americas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Panama plans to make its
the Colon Free Trade Zone (CFZ) one of the biggest in the American
hemisphere, the zone's general manager Pedro Campagnani said today.
</P>
<P>
The strategy to turn the CFZ into one of the biggest in the
continent is based on maintaining the competitive level and
restructuring commercial operations, he said.
</P>
<P>
The zone, some 80 kilometers west of this capital, will have a
18.3 million U.S. dollar budget, he said.
</P>
<P>
It has become an important point for international trade among
Asia, Europe, Latin America and the rest of the American
continent, he said.
</P>
<P>
Campagnani said that a process of modernization based on new
techniques and customs systems improve the service quality in the
zone.
</P>
<P>
He said that an additional budget of 721,000 dollars has been
approved to guarantee the zone's competitivity. 
