<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sichuan Province of China Still Powerful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan
province remains a powerhouse in terms of talent, labour and
resources, although Chongqing Municipality has been seperated from
it.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by leading officials of the Sichuan
provincial government here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
On March 14, China's legislative body -- the National People's
Congress -- approved a resolution on the establishment of
Chongqing Municipality. With three cities and one
prefecture, Chongqing Municipality now is the fourth and the
largest in China.
</P>
<P>
By losing Chongqing, Sichuan lost more than one-quarter of its
arable land, population and economic indexes.
</P>
<P>
However, Sichuan is still the country's third most populous
province with a population of 83.57 million, accounting for 6.8
percent of China's total.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the gross domestic product (GDP) of Sichuan, without
taking into consideration Chongqing's three cities and one
prefecture, was 298.5 billion yuan (36 billion US dollars),
ranking eighth in Chin.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Sichuan's live pig output ranked first in China and
its grain output ranked third. The output value of its
agriculture, forestry, animal husbandry and fisheries ranked sixth.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan's water resources total 140 million kilowatts, ranking
first in the country.
</P>
<P>
In Sichuan's Pangxi region, an average of 2.86 million kilowatt
hours of electricity can be generated per square kilometer.
</P>
<P>
Based on this output, the region is very likely to become
China's largest hydropower base.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan's reserves of 11 kinds of minerals rank first in China.
They include vanadium, titanium, lithium and silver. Its vanadium
and titanium account for 69 percent and 91 percent of China's
total respectively.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan abounds in tourist resources. Of China's seven scenic
spots included in the List of World Heritages of the United
Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization, three
are in Sichuan.
</P>
<P>
To cope with Sichuan's new situation after Chongqing became a
municipality, Sichuan has formulated a new development strategy
for its national economy at the turn of the century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
