<HEADLINE> Guerrillas Threaten to Thwart Colombian Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 1,879
candidates in 11 municipalities have withdrawn their names from
Sunday's election ballots after the Revolutionary Armed Forces of
Colombia (FARC) and the National Liberation Army (ELN) threatened
to sabotage the elections.
</P>
<P>
Colombian Guerrillas have threatened to thwart Sunday's
elections in 131 municipalities.
</P>
<P>
Since April of this year, The FARC and the ELN have
assassinated 51 mayors and councilmen and 37 candidates.
</P>
<P>
A National Civil Registry communique said there are no
candidates running for the office of mayor in 96 municipalities,
while in another 24, there are no candidates running for the
office of councilman. Governors and deputies of local assemblies,
however, will be elected there.
</P>
<P>
In the remaining 120 municipalities, only those names already
on the ballot can be elected to office, said the NCR.
</P>
<P>
</P>
