<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese National Games Concludes in Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The Eighth Chinese National
Games has proved to be a world-class sports meet as quite a few
world and Asian records were broken with all the competitions
concluded here Thursday evening.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the weightlifting competitions, the first world
record was surpassed in the swimming pool when the 16-year-old
Chen Yan broke the 15-year-old world record in the women's 400
meters individual medley by clocking four minutes and 34.79
secoinds.
</P>
<P>
Wu Yanyan, 19, followed suit to beat the women's 200m
individual medley with a time of 2:09.72.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese swimmers also bettered nine Asian records and 12
national marks. And 10 gold medalists clocked the year-best times
in the women's events.
</P>
<P>
The men swimmers also made striking progresses by entering the
world top ten in five events.
</P>
<P>
In the track competitions, three women athletes surpassed the
world mark in the heats and two bettered the newly-established
record in the finals of the women's 5,000 meters.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Bo clocked 14:28.09 and her teammate Dong Yongmei ran in
14:29.82 for a one-two finish for Liaoning province, their timings
all shattered the new record of 14:31.27 set by Dong in the heats.
</P>
<P>
The original mark of 14:36.45 was set up by Fernanda Ribeiro of
Portugal in Hechtel, Belgium on July 22, 1995.
</P>
<P>
Early, Jiang Bo won the women's 1,500m in 3:50.98, only 0.52
second shy of the world record.
</P>
<P>
Xiao Yanling, 29, won the women's discus title with a throw of
70 meters, the best result over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Li Xuemei, 20, broke the 11 seconds barrier in the women's 100
meters, claiming the gold medal in 10.79 seconds, the year's
second best time.
</P>
<P>
Chinese strongwomen displayed their dominance by breaking all
the world records in their nine categories while their man peers
also surpassed six world marks in their 10-class competitions.
</P>
<P>
However, the Chinese athletes were encouraged by the sports
officials to keep training for top forms in the world arena, as
the competitive atmosphere abroad will be more tough. 
</P>
</TEXT>
