<HEADLINE> Czech Foreign Minister Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Czech Foreign Minister Josef
Zieleniec Thursday resigned unexpectedly, saying that he found it
difficult to carry out his duties.
</P>
<P>
President Vaclav Havel accepted Zieleniec's resignation after
consulting with Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus.
</P>
<P>
Zieleniec, 51, who has been the foreign minister since January
1993, told a news conference that he was also quitting as deputy
chairman of the ruling Civic Democratic Party (ODS) headed by
Klaus.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on his resignation, Zieleniec said his power in
decision making on major policies of the ODS was limited, and that
gave him little choice but to resign.
</P>
<P>
The resignation, which showed the intensity of internal
conflicts in the ODS, was responsible for a slight devaluation of
the country's koruna, which moved from 18.55 koruny against one
Deutsche Mark to 18.64.
</P>
<P>
Jaroslav Sedivy, Ambassador to Belgium and the North Atlantic
Treaty Organization (NATO), will reportedly assume the post of
foreign minister. 
</P>
