<HEADLINE> Beijing Lifts Price Controls on Cabbage (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Beijing is to lift price
controls on Chinese cabbage tomorrow to put this staple vegetable
under market controls, the municipal government has announced
recently.
</P>
<P>
The cabbage is the only item from the grocer's shelf still
under government controls in the capital, so the new measure will
completely free Beijing's vegetables from the controls of the
planned economy.
</P>
<P>
The end of autumn marks the time for China's northerners to
start stocking up on cabbages because of the vegetable shortages
in winter. More than 100 kg. of cabbage are usually needed to get a
family through the winter, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Although the demand for cabbage has declined in recent years,
people still cart it home in large quantities when the season
comes this year.
</P>
<P>
Thirteen thousand hectares of cabbage have been planted in
Beijing this year, and the cabbage will be on the market at
the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The city is prepared for the price control removal,
according to Tao Zhiqiang, a city government official. With a
large variety of vegetables to choose from in winter, he said,
cabbage's status as the main family dish is in decline.
</P>
<P>
Cabbages now account for only one fifth of the vegetable sales
on the Beijing market.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
