<HEADLINE> More Container Business for East China Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Qingdao Port in east China's
Shandong province is expected to have a handling capacity of one
million TEUs this year, second only to Shanghai Port.
</P>
<P>
This was announced recently by Chang Dechuan, Port
Administration director, who said that, during the
January-September period, Qingdao handled more than 750,000
TEUs.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the port handled 810,000 TEUs, making
it 42nd among the world's top 100 container ports.
</P>
<P>
The century-old port has the country's only dock that can
handle the fifth generation of container ships. It handles half a
million TEUs annually.  
