<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Legal Immigrants Increase in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The number of legal immigrants in
Italy has been rising and is expected to reach 1.2 million by the
end of 1997, 100,000 more than 1996.
</P>
<P>
Figures released today by the Rome chapter of the international
Catholic charity, Caritas, said European immigrants, mainly from
eastern Europe, accounted for 40 percent of this total. Africans
made up 30 percent, Asians 18 percent and North and South
Americans 12 percent.
</P>
<P>
More than 119,000 Moroccans form the largest section of the
immigrant population in Italy. Half of the legal immigrants live
in northern Italy and Rome absorbs the most foreigners with about
199,433, 18.2 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
An increasingly large number of foreigners have been granted
residency for work reasons or for family reunions. 
</P>
