<HEADLINE> Economic Growth Picks Up in Chinese Island City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The economy of Haikou, the
capital of China's Hainan province, has been growing at an
accelerated pace this year, and is greater than for any comparable
period since 1993, said Leng Xiaoming, deputy mayor in charge of
economic work.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that Haikou's municipal GDP was 6.9
billion yuan (about 830 million US dollars) during the
January-September period, with 4.8 billion yuan in industrial
output value.
</P>
<P>
Haikou's state-owned industrial sector grew 14.1 percent in the
first nine months and the collective-owned industry a large 37
percent.
</P>
<P>
Leng said that Haikou's economic quality has also improved,
with state-owned enterprises getting more than 12 million yuan in
profits in the eight months to August, compared with over 70
million yuan in losses for the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
In the first nine months, Haikou put 2.2 billion yuan into
fixed assets, according to Leng, and he predicts that the annual
figure will reach 6.6 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
