stock market's fall and the downgrading of Asian stocks by the
U.S.-based investment bank Morgan Stanley.
</P>
<P>
Business World
</P>
<P>
-- The U.S. government is offering a loan guarantee program to
entice Philippine importers, who are grappling with soaring
interest rates, to bring in American goods.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Star
</P>
<P>
-- Defense Secretary Fortunato Abat assured Thursday that the
military would not launch an offensive against Camp Abubakar, main
headquarters of the Moro Islamic Liberation Front in Maguindanao
Province, the southern Philippines.  
</P>
