<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Commonwealth Summit to Be Held in Edinburgh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
EDINBURGH, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The 31st Commonwealth Heads
of Government Meeting (CHOGM) will be held in Edinburgh from
Friday, with the focus on promoting closer economic and trade
cooperation among the 54 Commonwealth countries.
</P>
<P>
During the four-day meeting, the Commonwealth leaders are
expected to discuss the particular theme of "Trade, Investment and
Development: The Road to Commonwealth Prosperity".
</P>
<P>
They will also discuss Nigeria's suspended membership, the
future role of the Commonwealth Ministerial Action Group (AMAG)
and the criteria for Commonwealth membership, according to British
government sources.
</P>
<P>
Highlighting the host country's initiative on the Commonwealth
Summit, British Prime Minister Tony Blair Wednesday urged for
closer Commonwealth trade cooperation in an effort to modernize
the institution.
</P>
<P>
Blair told the Commonwealth Business Forum in London that all
the Commonwealth member states should set out "a vision for a new
Commonwealth".
</P>
<P>
"I am determined that it should be a historic turning point for
the Commonwealth. An opportunity to modernize the institution and
prepare it for a new century," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
